metadata.title: How to Setup Minimum Order Value or Maximum Order Value? | Dukaan® Help Center
metadata.doc: How to Setup Minimum Order Value or Maximum Order Value? | Dukaan® Help CenterGo to DukaanGo to DukaanAll CollectionsPluginsHow to Setup Minimum Order Value or Maximum Order Value?How to Setup Minimum Order Value or Maximum Order Value?Learn how to add a minimum order value or maximum order value using the Bag Control pluginNWritten by Namrata Sawhney Updated over a week agoIn order to set a minimum or maximum order value to place orders on your store, you can use the Bag Control plugin. With this plugin, you can set limits on the total bag value, regardless of the number of products or the total weight of the products. Navigate to the Plugins section on your Dukaan web dashboard and search forBag Control Click on the Install Plugin button You will see the below screen.Here, you can choose to set any of the following limits:Set only minimum order value limitCustomers can not place an order if the total bag value is less than the limit set.Set only maximum order value limitCustomers can not place an order if the total bag value is more than the limit setSet both minimum and maximum order value limitCustomers can not place an order if the total bag value is less than or more than the total limit setOnce done, click on the Save changes button to add the limits to your Dukaan store.Read MoreHow to use the Nudgify plugin?How to use the Mailmunch plugin?How to use All-in-One SEO plugin? Did this answer your question?😞😐😃Dukaan® for PCPrivacy PolicyAbout Dukaan®FacebookTwitterLinkedInIntercomWe run on Intercom

metadata.doc: Can I get a replacement for a product? | Dukaan® Help CenterGo to DukaanGo to DukaanAll CollectionsBuyerCan I get a replacement for a product?Can I get a replacement for a product?NWritten by Namrata Sawhney Updated over a week agoAbout MyDukaan: We help businesses create their own online store and sell products online. Products sold from these stores are not owned by (MyDukaan.io) We are just providing a technology solution to help setup online store and sell products online. Now How do I get replacement the product? You must have received order updates on your WhatsApp/SMS which also includes seller contact details. Request you to call the seller directly from there and ask for a replacement directly from the seller itself.Did this answer your question?😞😐😃Dukaan® for PCPrivacy PolicyAbout Dukaan®FacebookTwitterLinkedInIntercomWe run on Intercom

metadata.title: Bulk upload for Advance Catalogue | Dukaan® Help Center
metadata.doc: ID: Enter the SKU Id of the variant of the product. Variant weight: Enter the weight of the variant of the product. Variant final selling price: Enter the final selling price of the product. Variant display price: Enter the MRP of the product. Variant weight unit: Choose the appropriate weight unit for the product from the drop-down menu. Product GST/Tax Value ( Percentage): Add the tax percentage you will be charging for the product. EAN/HSN Code: Enter the EAN/HSN code of the product. Product Images: To add images of your product, enter the image link of your product.(Note: Entering the location of the product on your system will not work.) SEO title: Enter an SEO-optimized meta title for your product. SEO description: Enter an SEO-optimized meta description for your product. (Note: Entering data in the SEO categories will enable the SEO plugin and add the values accordingly) Once you have all the details, save the file. In the Bulk add products screen, click on Add file button to upload the file.  A dialogue box will appear, here select the file which you just saved and click on the Upload button. Once the file is uploaded, you’ll see a preview of all the products that you’ll be adding. You can review the products you have uploaded and see if there are any errors.After reviewing, click on Save and add products button at the bottom.   Did this answer your question?😞😐😃Dukaan® for PCPrivacy PolicyAbout Dukaan®FacebookTwitterLinkedInIntercomWe run on Intercom

metadata.doc: How to download the QR code? | Dukaan® Help CenterGo to DukaanGo to DukaanAll CollectionsStore ProfileHow to download the QR code?How to download the QR code?Learn how to download the QR code for your storeNWritten by Namrata Sawhney Updated over a week agoStore QR code helps customers to easily find your business and place orders without any hassle of typing links in the web browser. Now you can get your own store’s QR Code with a single click. To get the QR code, click on Manage and then select Store QR Code. You’ll see the store QR code, which you can download or share directly with your customers by clicking on the Print PDF button.  You can take the print of this QR code and put them up inside your store, which will help customers to place their orders and help them to skip the queue. Or, this can be printed on flyers, pamphlets and can be distributed offline for your store promotion.Did this answer your question?😞😐😃Dukaan® for PCPrivacy PolicyAbout Dukaan®FacebookTwitterLinkedInIntercomWe run on Intercom

metadata.title: How to enable online payments on Mobile? | Dukaan® Help Center
metadata.doc: How to enable online payments on Mobile? | Dukaan® Help CenterGo to DukaanGo to DukaanAll CollectionsPaymentsHow to enable online payments on Mobile?How to enable online payments on Mobile?NWritten by Namrata Sawhney Updated over a week agoTo enable online payments for your store go to the Manage section, click on Online Payments and then verify your UPI ID or Bank Account. Once verified, you can now accept online payments on your store. You can also set custom payment methods like:1. Cash on Delivery - Your store will only accept Cash on Delivery orders.2. Online Payments - Your store will only accept online payments via UPI/Debit/Credit Cards or Net Banking.3. Both Options (Recommended) - You will be able to accept payments via Cash on Delivery or UPI/Debit/Credit Cards or Netbanking. Transaction Charges:We charge the following processing fees on online transactions. Also, the maximum transaction charges are capped to Rs. 150 per transaction. This means that you won't be paying more than Rs. 150 on transaction charges if the order amount is big.PlanOnline Payments Transaction ChargesGold1.49%Silver2.99%Read this to know how to set up online payments and complete KYC to increase the transaction limit on online payments. If you have any questions regarding the payments, get in touch with us at support@mydukaan.io now.Read MoreHow to use online payments for your store?How to do KYC to increase the payment limit?How to use the payment link to accept online payment on COD orders? metadata.doc: How to create a category? | Dukaan® Help CenterGo to DukaanGo to DukaanAll CollectionsProductsHow to create a category?How to create a category?Lear how to add categories in your storeNWritten by Namrata Sawhney Updated over a week agoCategorizing all your products can be helpful by organizing products in your store.First of all, head over to the Products section and then swipe left or click to open the Categories section. Next, click on Add new category button and enter the category name and image for that category and click Create button at the bottom. That's it! Your category has been created. Now while adding products, you can choose the relevant products and add them to their category. You can even create new categories while adding products by tapping on "Product Category" and you can click on "Add new category" to create a new category.Did this answer your question?😞😐😃Dukaan® for PCPrivacy PolicyAbout Dukaan®FacebookTwitterLinkedInIntercomWe run on Intercom

metadata.title: How to use the product attributes plugin? | Dukaan® Help Center
metadata.doc: . When the product information opens, (if your plugin has been activated) either scroll to the bottom of the page or click on Filters (If you've activated the advanced catalog function) or Attributes (If the advanced catalog function has not been activated) in the quick navigation menu.  Here you can select the desired attributes or create a new one as per your requirement.  To add an attribute for a product, click on Edit or add attributes. Upon clicking this button you will be able to select the attributes.  After you've selected the attributes, click on Select. If you want to add more attributes, click on Edit or add attributes. Clicking on this button will redirect you to the plugin dashboard. After assigning attributes to the products, this is how your storefront will look.  The highlighted region consists of the attributes you've provided. The customer can select any of the attributes you have provided. Upon selecting the desired attributes, the customer will be shown a filtered result. In the below image, the highlighted region consists of the chosen attributes. How to delete the attributes?If you wish to delete attributes, click on the Delete symbol beside the attribute value. Upon clicking the button, the following screen will appear. Here a disclaimer will be stating that the attribute will be permanently deleted.   If you still wish to go ahead, click on the checkbox stating that the action cannot be undone. Then, click on Yes, remove to delete the attribute.
